7.2 Supplier Relationship

Objective: Maintain secure supplier relationships throughout engagement lifecycle
1. Onboarding and Offboarding Security
Ensure Security of Onboarding/Offboarding via SLA:
Onboarding Procedures:
Security Verification:
- Background checks completed
- Security training provided
- NDA signed
- Acceptable use policy acknowledged
- Security incident reporting trained
- Contact information verified
Access Provisioning:
- Minimum necessary access only
- Time-limited access grants
- MFA enrollment
- VPN configuration
- Dedicated accounts (no shared)
- Access approval documented
Technical Integration:
- Network connectivity established
- Firewall rules configured
- Monitoring enabled
- Logging configured
- Backup integration
- Testing completed
Offboarding Procedures:
Access Revocation:
- Immediate upon contract end
- All access types revoked: 
	- Network access
	- Application access
	- Physical access
	- Email access
	- Cloud access
	- VPN access
- Account deletion/disablement
- Certificate revocation
- Token return
Knowledge Transfer:
- Documentation delivery
- System passwords changed
- Configuration information provided
- Support transition
- Data return/deletion
Security Verification:
- Access revocation confirmed
- Data deletion certified
- Equipment returned
- Intellectual property secured
- Final security review
2. Access Restrictions
Restrict Access to Minimum Necessary:
Access Principles:
- Least privilege
- Need-to-know
- Time-limited
- Purpose-specific
- Regularly reviewed
- Just-in-time provisioning
Access Controls:
Access Type
Restrictions
Monitoring
Network
Dedicated VPN, specific IP ranges
Connection logging, bandwidth monitoring
Systems
Specific systems only, no lateral movement
Session recording, activity logging
Data
Read-only preferred, limited write access
Data access logging, DLP
Administrative
Break-glass only, time-limited
Real-time alerting, video recording
3. Secure Remote Connections
Secure Dedicated Remote Connections:
Remote Access Requirements:
- Dedicated VPN tunnels
- Certificate-based authentication
- MFA mandatory
- Unique credentials (no sharing)
- Session time limits
- Idle timeout
- Jump host/bastion required
- No direct Internet access from systems
- Network segmentation
- Full session logging
Connection Security:
- Strong encryption (AES-256)
- Perfect forward secrecy
- TLS 1.2+ for all connections
- SSH key-based authentication
- No split-tunneling
- Device compliance checking
4. Incident Reporting
Define Incident Reporting and Response Procedures:
Supplier Incident Reporting Requirements:
What Must Be Reported:
- Security incidents affecting your data
- Suspected data breaches
- System compromises
- Malware detections
- Unauthorized access attempts
- Service outages
- Vulnerability discoveries
- Third-party breaches affecting services
- Regulatory investigations
- Law enforcement requests
Reporting Timelines:
- Critical incidents: Immediate (within 1 hour)
- High severity: 4 hours
- Medium severity: 24 hours
- Low severity: 48 hours
- Routine security updates: Monthly
Reporting Format:
- Initial notification (brief facts)
- Detailed incident report (within SLA)
- Regular updates during incident
- Final root cause analysis
- Remediation plan
- Lessons learned
Incident Response Procedures:
Roles and Responsibilities:
- Supplier incident commander
- Your organization liaison
- Communication protocols
- Escalation procedures
- Decision authority
- Coordination mechanisms
Response Activities:
- Containment measures
- Evidence preservation
- Forensic investigation
- Regulatory notifications
- Customer communications
- Remediation implementation
