8. Cyber-Educate Your Staff


8.1 Strategy

Objective: Build a culture of cybersecurity awareness through strategic training approaches
1. Train by Role
Role-Based Training Approach:
Role-Specific Training Needs:
Clinical Staff (Physicians, Nurses):
- EHR security best practices
- Patient data protection
- Mobile device security
- Secure messaging
- Recognizing medical device tampering
- Incident reporting (patient safety focus)
- Telemedicine security
Administrative Staff:
- Email security and phishing
- Document handling
- Secure printing
- Clean desk policy
- Password management
- Social engineering awareness
- Phone-based scams
IT Staff:
- Advanced threat detection
- Incident response procedures
- Secure configuration
- Vulnerability management
- Security tool operation
- Forensics basics
- Secure coding (developers)
Management/Executive:
- Cyber risk governance
- Incident command
- Business impact understanding
- Regulatory requirements
- Board reporting
- Decision-making during incidents
- Third-party risk management
Reception/Front Desk:
- Visitor management
- Social engineering awareness
- Phone verification procedures
- Physical security
- Suspicious behavior reporting
2. Adapt Content to Audience
Customization Principles:
Adaptation Factors:
- Technical proficiency level
- Job responsibilities
- Risk exposure
- Language preferences
- Learning styles
- Time availability
- Cultural considerations
